The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2707939918FFA7FE00515F6028EF73" box="[446,549,1303,1327]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Micardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953A0029918FFA7FE00515F6028EF73" box="[446,549,1303,1327]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Micardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was placed by early authors to a heterogeneous assemblage Erastrianae (sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB601E19918FFA7FF2951746342EF0F" author="Hampson" box="[151,335,1339,1363]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1910) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum. Vol. 10. Taylor and Francis, London, 829 pp, xix, plates 148 - 173." type="book chapter" year="1910">
Hampson 
<number id="3DEF6E379918FFA7FEAD51736342EF0F" box="[275,335,1339,1363]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="1910.0">1910</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), later called Acontiinae (sensu auctorum). In the course of recent modifications of the classification of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C2707939918FFA7FE3B511763F5EF2B" box="[389,504,1375,1399]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Noctuidae</taxonomicName>
this assmeblage has been divided into the subfamilies Acontiinae, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2707939918FFA7FAB35117679AEF2B" box="[1293,1431,1375,1399]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Eustrotiinae">Eustrotiinae</taxonomicName>
, Boletobiinae, Aediinae, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2707939918FFA7FE0851CB605CEFC7" box="[438,593,1411,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Metoponiinae">Metoponiinae</taxonomicName>
and Sinocharinae, with some genera placed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2707939918FFA7FB2551CB6703EFC7" box="[1179,1294,1411,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Xyleninae">Xyleninae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB601E19918FFA7FA9A51CB62E2EFE3" author="Speidel" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Speidel, W., Fanger, H. &amp; Naumann, C. M. (1996) The phylogeny of the Noctuidae (Lepidoptera). Systematic Entomology, 21, 219 - 251." type="journal article" year="1996">
Speidel 
<emphasis id="B953A0029918FFA7FA3651CC62B9EFE3" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="3DEF6E379918FFA7FF0A51EF62E2EFE3" box="[180,239,1447,1471]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB601E19918FFA7FF4051EF6034EFE3" author="Fibiger" box="[254,569,1447,1471]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Fibiger, M. &amp; Lafontaine, J. D. (2005) A review of the higher classification of the Noctuoidea (Lepidoptera) with special reference to the Holarctic fauna. Esperiana, 11, 7 - 82." type="journal article" year="2005">
Fibiger &amp; Lafontaine 
<number id="3DEF6E379918FFA7FE4351EF6034EFE3" box="[509,569,1447,1471]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB601E19918FFA7FDF951EF618CEFE3" author="Lafontaine" box="[583,897,1447,1471]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Lafontaine, J. D. &amp; Fibiger, M. (2006) Revised higher classification of the Noctuoidea. Canadian Entomol ogist, 138, 610 - 635." type="journal article" year="2006">
Lafontaine &amp; Fibiger 
<number id="3DEF6E379918FFA7FCF851EF618CEFE3" box="[838,897,1447,1471]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB601E19918FFA7FC3151EF664EEFE3" author="Holloway" box="[911,1091,1447,1471]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2009) The Moths of Borneo, part 13, Family Noctuidae, subfamilies Pantheinae, Bagisarinae, Acontiinae, Aediinae, Eustrotiinae, Bryophilinae, Aeroperoninae, Aventiinae, Eublemminae, miscellaneous. Malayan Nature Journal, 62 (1 - 2), 1 - 240." type="journal article" year="2009">
Holloway 
<number id="3DEF6E379918FFA7FBB651EF664EEFE3" box="[1032,1091,1447,1471]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="2009.2011">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 2011; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB601E19918FFA7FB2551EF62DEEFBF" author="Lafontaine" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Lafontaine J. D. &amp; Schmidt, B. C. (2010) Annotated check list of the Noctuoidea (Insecta, Lepidoptera) of North America north of Mexico. ZooKeys, 40, 1 - 239." type="journal article" year="2010">
Lafontaine &amp; Schmidt 
<number id="3DEF6E379918FFA7FF29518362DEEFBF" box="[151,211,1483,1507]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Zahiri 
<emphasis id="B953A0029918FFA7FE9151846367EFBF" box="[303,362,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="3DEF6E379918FFA7FECA518363F4EFBF" box="[372,505,1483,1507]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="2010.2011">2010, 2011</number>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB601E19918FFA7FDB051836095EFBF" author="Ueda" box="[526,664,1483,1507]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Ueda, K. (1984) A revision of the genus Deltote R. L. and its allied genera from Japan and Taiwan (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae, Acontiinae). Pt 1. A generic classification of the genus Deltote R. L. and its allied genera. Bull. Kitakyushu nat. Hist. Mus. 5, 91 - 133." type="journal article" year="1984">
Ueda (
<number id="3DEF6E379918FFA7FDE251836095EFBF" box="[604,664,1483,1507]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="1984.1987">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB601E19918FFA7FD18518360D2EFBF" author="Ueda" box="[678,735,1483,1507]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Ueda, K. (1987) A revision of the genus Deltote R. L. and its allied genera from Japan and Taiwan (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae, Acontiinae). Pt 2. Systematics of the genus Deltote R. L. and its allied genera. Bull. Kitakyushu nat. Hist. Mus. 6, 1 - 117." type="journal article" year="1987">1987</bibRefCitation>
) placed 
<taxonomicName id="4C2707939918FFA7FCFA518361A6EFBF" box="[836,939,1483,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Micardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953A0029918FFA7FCFA518361A6EFBF" box="[836,939,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Micardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into 
<taxonomicName id="4C2707939918FFA7FC5551836633EFBF" box="[1003,1086,1483,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Deltote" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953A0029918FFA7FC5551836633EFBF" box="[1003,1086,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Deltote</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. Presently this group is considered as a core of the modern subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C2707939918FFA7FD2651A7612FEC5B" box="[664,802,1519,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Eustrotiinae">Eustrotiinae</taxonomicName>
, and therefore we consider 
<taxonomicName id="4C2707939918FFA7FBEA51A766B6EC5B" box="[1108,1211,1519,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Micardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953A0029918FFA7FBEA51A766B6EC5B" box="[1108,1211,1519,1543]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Micardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a member of this subfamily.
</paragraph>
